2.title: An Ayuthaya Apology
2.plot: Evita and Tyler escape to the spiritual city of Ayutthaya as they work out their differences. Meanwhile, JP and Jeremiah search for a place to live in Bangkok's backpacker district. Jeremiah blows a job interview, and the gang must decide whether to stick it out in Bangkok or make a hasty exit on the night train.

3.title: What You Can Do in Chiang Mai
3.plot: The cast arrives in Chiang Mai, lured by the promise of jobs and housing, only to find that nothing is what it seems. Quickly losing money, they seek advice from anyone who can help including fellow traveler Rob Lloyd of StopHavingABoringLife.com and the legendary "cave monk" of Chiang Mai. JP searches for housing and transportation, eventually finding a motorbike. The cast plays with live tigers at Tiger Kingdom.

1.title: Arrival
1.plot: Jet Set Zero founders Matt, Rob, Brian, and Dan discuss their inspiration for the show, their goals and ambitions, and their desire to inspire others to travel and not be held back by life. The team packs up their lives in Seattle and flies to Vietnam.

2.title: Settling In
2.plot: As they adjust to life in a developing country, the cast tries to navigate the chaos in the city of Saigon. Feeling discouraged, they begin to second guess their choice of Saigon as a viable first location, as they encounter difficulties in finding jobs and housing.

3.title: Nha Trang
3.plot: After a stressful first couple of days in Vietnam, the cast decides to leave the city for a weekend trip to the countryside of Nha Trang. Trading in culture shock and jet lag for fun and relaxation, the cast takes an interesting ride on a night train, has a surprising experience at a seafood restaurant, and finds some peace on the beach.

1.title: I Never Thought I Would Travel
1.plot: 4 girls. 3 months. 1 city: Saigon. It's hot, exhausting, full of crazy traffic -- and they love it. As the girls battle with a greedy hotel landlord, Jen gets close with an Australian traveler.

2.title: Will Work for Travel
2.plot:

3.title: Delays
3.plot: The girls grapple with (not) finding love on the road. Jen says goodbye to Ben, as he heads back home to Sydney. Meanwhile, Serene sends a Vietnamese care package to her friend Hussein in Turkey while Kris haggles with the locals to get a good price on a motorbike.

4.title: Crazy Talk
4.plot: The cast learns about the traditional culture at a Buddhist "Naming of the Dead" ceremony. Finding it hard to meet local people, they attend LorettoFest, a festival of music with special guest Ratatat. Jen considers leaving early to visit Ben in Australia.

5.title: No Better Place to Be
5.plot: After Jen buys her plane ticket to Australia, the cast decides they'd like to take a break from the city. They visit a senior center and learn to be grateful for what they have. For Christmas, Laurene spends time in the local village of Mui Ne, while the other girls relax at the beach.

6.title: End of the Road
6.plot: Laurene continues her solo travels, visiting Phan Rang and learning about Buddhism. After a New Years Eve to remember, a fed-up Kris quits her job and prepares to leave Saigon for a month-long backpacking trip with Jen. Despite landing a tutoring job, Serene is out of money and makes a tough choice.

7.title: Wouldn't Change a Thing
7.plot: Jen and Kris begin their travels outside of Saigon. Before leaving, Kris goes to the pharmacy to load up on cheap drugs. Laurene goes to an orphanage and visits with children with disabilities. Reflecting on their experience in Saigon, Kris announces she will be heading to Myanmar by herself and Laurene will continue on to Ecuador with Jet Set Zero.

1.title: A Challenge
1.plot: Jet Set Zero's sixth season begins on a whole new continent. Freddie and Laurene arrive in Quito, Ecuador and discuss their goals and philosophies. The duo searches for an apartment and observes traditional Ecuadorian dance before climbing a mountain to check out an amazing sunset.

2.title: Wanted: Job, Security
2.plot: With the cast now completed, Ryan goes skateboarding with the locals, while Freddie begins his job hunt. The cast learns some startling news about the safety of their neighborhood - or lack thereof - but have a fun time celebrating Freddie's 28th birthday anyway.

3.title: Easy Come, Easy Go
3.plot: The cast grapples with the next challenge on their list - jobs. Laurene, Freddie and Jenna quickly find jobs, but keeping them is another matter entirely. Meanwhile Ryan sets out to see a different side of Quito, and Jenna deals with the realities of a relationship back at home.

4.title: Get Out of Town
4.plot: The cast decides it's time for some change. Freddie and Ryan head out of town to share an adventure with some British girls, while Jenna and Laurene explore the city with new friend/guest cast member Amy Cao.

5.title: Variety Packed
5.plot: The gang takes in the stunning beauty of Ecuador as they face their most challenging moments yet. When Ryan runs out of money, he's forced to stay at home while Freddie, Amy, and Jenna go horseback riding at the base of Mt. Cotopaxi. Upon returning, the cast discovers that Ryan isn't the only one with serious financial problems.

6.title: One Door Opens...
6.plot: Are travelers more spiritually aware? The cast splits as they search for answers to some of life's most ancient questions. Jenna ventures into the jungles of Ecuador for a taste of hallucinogenic ayahuasca, while Freddie and Laurene embark on personal quests through some of Ecuador's beautiful Catholic churches. Ryan longs for that other great spiritual center: home.

7.title: Adiós!
7.plot: As one journey ends, new stories begin. Freddie, Jenna, and Laurene take one of their last trips outside of Quito to Isla de la Plata and reflect on their time in Ecuador. Through all the trials of Quito they've come to love their new home and embraced the Jet Set Zero lifestyle.

1.title: New Country, New Friends
1.plot: A brand new Jet Set Zero cast sets out to explore the countryside of Italy one stunning location at a time. Courtney and Lynne are the first to arrive in Bajardo and enjoy the ancient city before meeting up with Sarah and Perrin in San Remo. From here they get their introduction to their new jobs and life in Italy.

2.title: Week 2: Brescia
2.plot: As the girls finally meet up as a group they now set off to explore the local countryside and begin their jobs teaching with ACLE. Gorgeous vistas, delicious dinners, and farm life abound.
